wikipedia_page.main: George Carpenter (28 February 1818 – 3 June 1849) was an English first-class cricketer active 1838–1844 who played for Cambridge Town Club. He was born and died in Cambridge. A brother of Robert Carpenter, he appeared in nine first-class matches.

response: * George Carpenter, 1st Baron Carpenter (1657–1731), British soldier, MP and ambassador

* George Carpenter, 3rd Earl of Tyrconnell (1788–1812), British peer and soldier

|Made one first-class appearance for the Cambridge Town Club. Brother of George Carpenter. Another brother, Robert, played between the 1850s and 1870s and is considered one of the best batsmen of his era.
